        <div class="msgSubject">Mini-Guide for aspiring Armorsmiths! </div>
        <div class="sm notbold">
          
          Posted: 2010-11-09 19:40:47   | <input type="checkbox" name="quote-1289353247321791826" id="quote-1289353247321791826" class="msgQuoteCheck" onchange="multiQuote2()"/><label for="quote-1289353247321791826" onclick="multiQuote2()"> Quote</label>  | <a href="/forum.html?forum=190&amp;mid=1289353247321791826&amp;post=1&amp;replyto=1289353247321791826&amp;page=1" class="icon-replytothis" rel="nofollow">Reply to Post</a> | <a id="FOLLOW_MID_1289353247321791826" onclick="followToggle('add','1289353247321791826')" href="javascript:" class="icon-follow">Follow</a> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName Scholar" href="/users/Mireli">Mireli</a><div class="msgWhoTitle Scholar">Scholar</div></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">843 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Decent  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">Hi there, <br /> <br />I made my way to 50 with complete trial and error, and if I could do things again I would stock up on a lot of different items. This post is to help those on their way up and not have to go through the mistakes I made =) <br /> <br />This is basically a list of items to stock up on that you will find yourself making for zero EXP at later levels. While it may not be as efficient to level off of these items, it will help you out more in the future. <br /> <br />These are only the stuff you can actually make, there is a lot of others that I keep stacks of from Leatherworking/Weaving as well =) <br /> <br />I left out the obvious things (Rivets, Buckles, etc) as you generally want to make these when they give no experience for the additional HQ chance. <br /> <br />I hope this helps =) <br /> <br />PS: I don't know the exact levels you should be doing these at, if anyone can help me with this information let me know and I can add it =) <br /> <br /><b>Things you will need infinity-million of:</b> <br /> <br />Iron Ingot (So many. Mainly for Plates, though) <br />Iron Plate (So many. So, so many. Please kill me now for not having these made) <br />Iron Chain (The bane of my existence. I've used hundreds of these) <br />Iron Rings (Mainly used for Sleeves/Vest but also important for pesky repairs) <br />Bronze Chain (Mainly for Sleeves, they stack easier though, so may be better to just use these to save space) <br />Bronze Plate (I ended up just buying these for 6600 from an NPC, can save a lot of Gil by making them early) <br />Bronze Rings (Worth keeping some for repairs and Sleeve Making) <br />Brass Plate (Used for a bunch of gear, ended up making tons with Hasty Hands) <br />Brass Ingot (Used in a multitude of things, but I honestly get enough from Leves) <br /> <br /><b>If you plan on making the R38 Bronze Set, stock up on stacks of 12 of these or however many you are planning on making while they give EXP:</b> <br /> <br />Bronze Backplate <br />Bronze Breastplate <br />Bronze Couters <br />Bronze Cuisses <br />Bronze Rerebraces <br />Bronze Poelyns <br />Bronze Greaves <br />Bronze Neck Guard <br />Bronze Chain Sleeves <br /> <br /><b>If you plan on making Iron Haubergeons, Cavalry Haubergeons and other high end equipment:</b> <br /> <br />Iron Chain Sleeves <br />Iron Chainmail Vest <br /> <br /><b>If you plan on making the Iron Full Plate set (Cuirass, Sabatons, Gauntlets). Very important to stock up on as they are for the highest level of gear. I spent hours last night making these with hasty hands... Make at least a stack of each material:</b> <br /> <br />Iron Backplate <br />Iron Breastplate <br />Iron Couters <br />Iron Cuisses <br />Iron Rerebraces <br />Iron Poelyns <br />Iron Greaves <br />Iron Neck Guard <br />Bronze Chain Sleeves (Yes, Bronze. You will need 2x the amount of these than the others) <br /> <br /><b>Some things you might grind on that you should keep a stack or two of, especially the random +1s:</b> <br /> <br />Iron Barbut Visor <br />Iron Sallet Visor<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Aurica Valentia - World First 50 Armorsmith <br /></div></div>
