      <div class="msgContentFrame">So basically, make 1-2 stacks of everything we can make, and save it. Honestly, this isn't that realistic considering how much space all of this junk would take up. You are better off holding onto stuff that you will EXP off of (like squares) than trying to hold onto items that stack in 12's for items to make to sell. I mean, just for says the Bronze Plate Chest alone, it would be taking up 3 spots in your retainer/inventory just for the Armorer crafted pieces. Then, you can add on another 3 spots for each of the other pieces. You are at 9 already, from just the armorer parts (which is half the recipe mats). You are better off just holding onto a stack of Bronze Nuggets, Bronze Squares and Ochre Leather Straps, they stack to 99 and is only 3 spots. Then you can just make the parts as you need them. <br /> <br />Sure, you get less SP, but you are also not focusing on SP when you are trying to make money, usually. Sure it is nice, but it isn't worth the 4-5x space requirements to hold onto everything, and space ... is a huge issue. <br /> <br />Maybe when we can get multiple retainers, or extra inventory/retainer space in the upcoming patches? Right now, I think I will stick to hoarding squares :P Leveling up is more important than making money right now, for me. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 12th 2010 10:20am by MattVid6 </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>[img]<a href="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png" title="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png" rel="external nofollow">http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png</a>[/img]</div></div>
