      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">RamseySylph wrote:</div><div class="orig">It's a guide, so it's about opinion, this is obviously a guide for someone who wants to make a profit while leveling, or at least not a loss. It's useful for some of us I am sure - if your space requirements are too large from playing other classes, then obviously you can't keep all of this in mind, but it's still a helpful post.</div></div> <br />You are just assuming I don't make any money, which is a poor assumption at that. Get above 18 and then come back and talk about space usage, you have no idea (2 plates, sheep leather and rivets are just the beginning). And just an FYI, most of the stuff you will be making from 18-25, you are going to be selling at a loss. I don't care what you say, selling Hauby's and chain gear at 20-50k is going to just dwindle your account to nothing, while netting next to no SP what so ever. And that is just the thing, if I can't sell the items for a profit, I simply say &quot;screw it&quot; and move on to grind on the cheapest things I can sell to the vendor. The economy is basically garbage in this game so far, as making a profit, has more to do with people finding your shop, period, than just making the items. <br /> <br />To make money, I simply make up all the materials I need, not worrying about the SP I am getting, and then I sell it. Though the items I shoot for, are items in my level range, so the SP is actually pretty decent anyways. Right now, I am making and selling colored Bronze Plate gear, the pieces seem to be selling like hot-cakes at 120-180k per piece, which is pretty good. And I am also getting 200-350 SP for the items it takes to make it, so the SP is actually really good. <br /> <br />I am just saying, following this guide WILL destroy your space in a matter of minutes. You can't possibly store all of this stuff, unless you are only leveling armorer and nothing else. You can store 99 squares for one space, or backplate, rerebraces, cuises, greaves, backplate, neck guard, and all this other stuff for just 3 pieces of the plate gear ... that would take up a total of 12 spaces (not including the leather/canvas parts). I hold onto the mats I can't make myself, which take up a ton of space, and then create the mats I can make on my own, as I need them. You just don't have enough room to hold all the armorer parts when there are 6 pieces per item you have to store. <br /> <br />But I have over 4 million gil, and like 20-30 stacks of iron squares. I am hemorrhaging money. I don't have anything to buy except more shards, so what is the point of making money right now? Just to say you have it? I literally spend next to nothing, and make it all back in a night of leves. <br /> <br />Then again, this patch next week is going to give us 40 more slots to work with (20 on character, 20 on retainer), so that will alleviate a large majority of the problems I am having now managing my iron square storage :) I will be able to store more materials for armorer, rather than just skill up mats. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 22nd 2010  2:51pm by MattVid6 </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>[img]<a href="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png" title="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png" rel="external nofollow">http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png</a>[/img]</div></div>
